4 SECTION 5. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - AUTONOMOUS TECHNOLOGY.
5 During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying the costs and
6 benefits of investing in autonomous technology infrastructure in the state. The study must
7 include an analysis of the industries using autonomous technology, future industries that may
8 use autonomous technology, the economic impact of autonomous technology, and the return on
9 investment to the state. The legislative management shall report its findings and
10 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
11 the seventieth legislative assembly.
